Foilers X Kannan Sanjay: Where car customization meets fashion brilliance! 😎

In a groundbreaking collaboration that bridges the realms of automotive excellence and fashion innovation, Foilers, the renowned car customization company, joins forces with the illustrious fashion icon, Kannan Sanjay. This dynamic partnership is the brainchild of longstanding friendship between H.E Aziz Barbhaya, the visionary owner of Foilers, and Sanjay, a trailblazer in the world of fashion. 

United by a shared passion for creativity and a shared history dating back to their childhood, these two visionaries have combined their expertise to create a reel that transcends the boundaries of traditional design.

Prepare to be enthralled as this reel unfolds, showcasing the extraordinary synergy between Foilers’ innovative car customization techniques and Kannan Sanjay’s unparalleled fashion sensibility. 

Together, they redefine the boundaries of design, inviting viewers on a visual journey where cars become canvases and fashion becomes an extension of one’s personality. 💯

Here’s presenting our very own & scintillating MTI INDIA “ GAYATRI INAMDAR “ the true essence of INDIA ; the power of Culture , Beauty & Togetherness @misstourisminternational @gayatrii_inamdar @nrityaafashionentertainment 

Promoting one of the most popular & historical tourism places in India “ LODHI GARDEN “ in New Delhi ; Lodhi Garden has an interesting history. The garden dates back to the 15th century and is named after the Lodi dynasty that ruled over Delhi once. In fact, the garden is also home to the tombs of several rulers from the Lodhi dynasty that are architectural marvels too. Spread over 90 acres (360,000 m2), it contains Mohammed Shah's Tomb, the Tomb of Sikandar Lodi, the Shisha Gumbad and the Bara Gumbad, architectural works of the 15th century by Lodis - who ruled parts of northern India and Punjab and Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province of modern-day Pakistan, from 1451 to 1526.
